definition: to regard as/to figure/to calculate/to compute

sentences.english: They've had their revenge more or less.
And you're thinking - at last, they get their comeuppance.
sentences.chinese: 你或许在想，他们总算是罪有应得了。

sentences.english: Finally be able to Ningmou moon.
We finally got some shut-eye after midnight.
sentences.chinese: 午夜过后我们总算睡了一会儿。

sentences.english: After a check Yu Xiaoji finally fix the faucet.
sentences.chinese: 经过一番检查余小奇总算修好了水龙头。

sentences.english: I’m glad to see we’re not just sitting around waiting for the undertaker.
sentences.chinese: 我很高兴，我们总算没有在这边坐着等死。

sentences.english: At the end, he ground out the enormous "Biography of George Washington".
sentences.chinese: 最后，他苦心经营总算写成卷帙浩繁的《华盛顿传》。

sentences.english: After working day after day, we can finish the work before it's due.
sentences.chinese: 加班，这项工作总算是可以刻期完成了。

sentences.english: Somehow she managed to provide her children with food and clothing.
sentences.chinese: 她总算设法使她之孩子有饭吃，有衣穿。

sentences.english: I said good riddance to the wild years of my early 20s.
sentences.chinese: 我总算打发掉了20多年前那段疯狂的日子。

sentences.english: Ninth 10 a while, now finally gather some facial.
sentences.chinese: 连输十一阵，如今总算捡回些颜面。

sentences.english: She finally knows about it. She's coming.
sentences.chinese: 她总算知道了，她过来了。

sentences.english: She somehow bumbled through four years of college.
sentences.chinese: 她总算乱混过了四年大学。

sentences.english: Well, the first week of school is finally over, so today I slept in.
sentences.chinese: 好吧，第一周的学习总算过去了，今天我要睡个懒觉。

sentences.english: He had by now an inkling of the factors involved.
sentences.chinese: 他总算对涉及到的各种因素略知一二了。

sentences.english: I managed to talk my way out of having to give a speech.
sentences.chinese: 我好说歹说总算逃脱了发言差事。

good and bad/most unfortunate occurrence/in any case/whatever
one breath/in one breath/at a stretch
